  "texts": [
    "Specifically, we modify y t only if |ℑ(y t)| is among the γ-smallest values in {|ℑ(y t)|} m t=1 and the sign of ℑ(y t) differs from 2ζ t -1.",
    "Furthermore, we shrink the imaginary part by a factor δ ∈ [-1, 1] to further limit the distortion:y wm t = ℜ(y t) -iδ • ℑ(y t), if ℑ(y t) • (2ζ t -1) < 0 and |ℑ(y t)| ≤ Quantile γ ({|ℑ(y t)|} m t=1), y t, otherwise,(2)and y wm p-t = y wm t. When γ = δ = 1, the soft variant (2) reduces to the hard sign flip (1); when γ = 0 and δ = -1, it reduces to no watermarking.",
    "In practice, varying (γ, δ) enables flexible control over the trade-off between watermark strength and data fidelity.",
    "For example, one can tune (γ, δ) to maximize detectability under a given distortion budget by performing a lightweight grid search over synthetic samples.",
